I'm going to mess around with finessing the visualizations here.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
renv::install("tidybayes")
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
library(tidybayes)
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
posterior_samples |> 
  pull(prob) |> 
  density() |> 
  tidy() |> 
  rename(prob = x, density = y) ->
  posterior_dens

posterior_dens |> 
  ggplot(aes(prob, density/max(density)))+
    geom_area(fill = "grey60")+
    geom_line(aes(y = posterior/max(posterior)),
              linetype = 2,
              data = grid)+
    theme(
      axis.title.y = element_blank(),
      axis.text.y = element_blank(),
      panel.grid.major.y = element_blank()
    )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Comparison of the kernel density estimate vs the actual posterior distribution.](index_files/figure-html/fig-dens-grid-1.png){#fig-dens-grid width=576}
:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
posterior_samples |> 
  median_hdci(prob, .width = c(0.5, 0.95)) ->
  intervals
intervals |> 
  gt() |> 
  fmt_number(decimals = 2)
```

